  "body": "This one is fun as well, so here I am, opening the chat selection view:\r\n\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-50-13](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159878275-c0220624-00d0-4e24-8507-ee3f61021af6.png)\r\n\r\nFrom here, I click the other button to open the context menu:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-50-51](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159878907-7aa1eefc-8ad8-4d23-9666-fb26ad341105.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFirs thing to note here: it seems that the trigger button loses part of its \"highlighted\" state when the menu is open but the button itself is no longer hovered. I think such a button should keep its \"highlighted\" state while the context menu is open. Will file a separate issue for that.\r\n\r\nAnyways, now I hover the first item of the context menu (You can't see the hover effect on the menu item because of me doing a screenshot):\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-52-53](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159878845-21153bad-5fd6-4616-a5ef-78baf8e581f2.png)\r\n\r\nNotice how both: the input and the button in the right screen have lost their placeholder and label respectively. This stay as it is while hovering menu items, until the context menu gets closed.\r\n\r\nMaybe some funny z-index issue?\r\n\r\n",
